and responsible monsters.

280
00:10:21,921 --> 00:10:23,223
Allan!

281
00:10:24,524 --> 00:10:25,658
(chuckles)

282
00:10:25,658 --> 00:10:26,926
Hard to believe, huh?

283
00:10:26,926 --> 00:10:29,395
Considering my past.

284
00:10:29,395 --> 00:10:30,363
(Genki whimpers)

285
00:10:30,363 --> 00:10:31,865
Huh, what's the matter?

286
00:10:31,865 --> 00:10:33,199
Got a stomach ache or something?

287
00:10:34,968 --> 00:10:36,603
Allan!

288
00:10:36,603 --> 00:10:37,904
It's unreal!

289
00:10:37,904 --> 00:10:40,140
You used to treat
monsters so badly.

290
00:10:40,140 --> 00:10:42,275
♪

291
00:10:42,275 --> 00:10:44,043
Whoa!

292
00:10:44,043 --> 00:10:45,445
I'm so proud of you.

293
00:10:45,445 --> 00:10:47,147
You've really changed.

294
00:10:47,147 --> 00:10:48,414
Come on, gee.

295
00:10:49,582 --> 00:10:50,984
Chi?

296
00:10:50,984 --> 00:10:52,218
Aw, you're the best.

297
00:10:52,218 --> 00:10:53,753
Come here, big guy.

298
00:10:54,888 --> 00:10:56,122
Get off me.

299
00:10:56,122 --> 00:10:58,091
Someone might be looking.

300
00:10:58,091 --> 00:10:59,359
You know, Allan?

301
00:10:59,359 --> 00:11:01,027
Those mystery disks
are lucky to have

302
00:11:01,027 --> 00:11:02,262
an ally like you.

303
00:11:03,429 --> 00:11:05,532
Which reminds me,
that Wood Golem fella

304
00:11:05,532 --> 00:11:07,200
seemed like a fierce enemy.

305
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,502
Aw, he doesn't scare me.

306
00:11:09,502 --> 00:11:12,906
Not with these strategies
I've come up with.

307
00:11:12,906 --> 00:11:14,474
Huh, where'd they go?

308
00:11:14,474 --> 00:11:16,009
Looking for these?

309
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:17,744
Ah, there they are.

310
00:11:17,744 --> 00:11:20,113
Thought I'd lost them.

311
00:11:20,113 --> 00:11:21,314
Ah.

312
00:11:21,314 --> 00:11:23,049
You were clutching
onto those things.

313
00:11:23,049 --> 00:11:25,051
You wouldn't even let go
while you were passed out.

314
00:11:25,051 --> 00:11:27,554
With these plans,
we can defeat anyone.

315
00:11:27,554 --> 00:11:29,923
If only the others had
followed my directions,

316
00:11:29,923 --> 00:11:31,991
we could've defeated
Wood Golem too,

317
00:11:31,991 --> 00:11:33,693
but they didn't.

318
00:11:33,693 --> 00:11:37,297
♪

319
00:11:37,297 --> 00:11:39,732
Genki, what do you say
after dinner we have

320
00:11:39,732 --> 00:11:43,036
ourselves a little
monster battle?

321
00:11:43,036 --> 00:11:44,537
Hold a battle?

322
00:11:44,537 --> 00:11:46,973
Sure, Mocchi
against Small Worm?

323
00:11:46,973 --> 00:11:49,442
What, that little thing?

324
00:11:49,442 --> 00:11:52,779
Don't underestimate him
or you'll be sorry.

325
00:11:52,779 --> 00:11:55,114
All right, you're on.

326
00:11:55,114 --> 00:11:56,716
Yeah, Chi!

327
00:11:56,716 --> 00:11:58,051
Everybody ready?

328
00:11:58,051 --> 00:11:59,419
This is a real match.

329
00:11:59,419 --> 00:12:03,289
♪

330
00:12:03,289 --> 00:12:06,526
So no holding back just
because we're all friends.

331
00:12:06,526 --> 00:12:08,094
You might regret it.

332
00:12:08,094 --> 00:12:09,896
Here's the plan, Mocch.

333
00:12:09,896 --> 00:12:11,331
Be constantly
on the move,

334
00:12:11,331 --> 00:12:13,199
and wear Small Worm out.

335
00:12:13,199 --> 00:12:14,367
Chi!

336
00:12:14,367 --> 00:12:15,868
Go, Worm!

337
00:12:15,868 --> 00:12:18,805
♪

338
00:12:18,805 --> 00:12:20,607
(Small Worm growls)

339
00:12:20,607 --> 00:12:31,317
♪

340
00:12:31,317 --> 00:12:33,253
Yeah nice moves, Mocch.

341
00:12:33,253 --> 00:12:38,825
♪

342
00:12:38,825 --> 00:12:40,460
(Small Worm bleats)

343
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:42,161
♪

344
00:12:42,161 --> 00:12:45,265
Exactly as we planned, you're
wearing the opponent down.

345
00:12:45,265 --> 00:12:47,900
♪

346
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:49,736
(Mocchi laughing)

347
00:12:49,736 --> 00:12:52,272
♪

348
00:12:52,272 --> 00:12:55,375
Okay, your next move is this.

349
00:12:55,375 --> 00:12:56,676
Right, Chi.

350
00:12:56,676 --> 00:12:58,611
Double‐pounder!

351
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:00,046
(Small Worm wails)

352
00:13:00,046 --> 00:13:01,814
Yeah, did it.

353
00:13:01,814 --> 00:13:03,182
Chi!

354
00:13:03,182 --> 00:13:05,418
Now, this one
will mean the match.

355
00:13:05,418 --> 00:13:07,320
Cherry blossom blizzard.

356
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:09,355
(Mocchi shouts)

357
00:13:09,355 --> 00:13:11,324
♪

358
00:13:11,324 --> 00:13:13,326
Small Worm, don't give up!

359
00:13:13,326 --> 00:13:14,560
♪

360
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:16,663
Cherry blossom blizzard.

361
00:13:16,663 --> 00:13:21,134
♪

362
00:13:21,134 --> 00:13:22,468
After him!

363
00:13:22,468 --> 00:13:23,803
Move!

364
00:13:23,803 --> 00:13:27,006
♪

365
00:13:27,006 --> 00:13:29,342
Mocchi.

366
00:13:29,342 --> 00:13:30,677
Snap out of it.

367
00:13:30,677 --> 00:13:31,844
Don't worry, Genki.

368
00:13:31,844 --> 00:13:33,880
He just got the wind
knocked out of him.

369
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:36,382
Mocchi fine, Chi.

370
00:13:36,382 --> 00:13:38,451
Ah, Mocchi.

371
00:13:38,451 --> 00:13:40,653
Just give us a few minutes
so Mocchi can rest up,

372
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:42,789
then we'll pick up
the match where we left off.

373
00:13:42,789 --> 00:13:44,290
Hmm, no.

374
00:13:44,290 --> 00:13:45,992
I'm afraid you two
don't have what it takes

375
00:13:45,992 --> 00:13:47,193
to beat Small Worm.

376
00:13:47,193 --> 00:13:48,461
Wanna bet?

377
00:13:48,461 --> 00:13:49,529
Don't you get it?

378
00:13:49,529 --> 00:13:51,230
Why he...

379
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:54,367
No, why <i>you</i> lost the match?

380
00:13:54,367 --> 00:13:55,635
Huh?

381
00:13:55,635 --> 00:13:56,836
Thought so.

382
00:13:56,836 --> 00:13:58,538
And as long as you
can't figure that out,

383
00:13:58,538 --> 00:14:00,540
you won't beat
Wood Golem either.

384
00:14:03,109 --> 00:14:04,243
Ah.

385
00:14:04,243 --> 00:14:05,378
Don't leave me!

386
00:14:05,378 --> 00:14:06,446
Come on.

387
00:14:06,446 --> 00:14:09,015
(Allan grunts)

388
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:12,919
Be true to yourself,
like you used to be.

389
00:14:12,919 --> 00:14:14,821
Let's go, Worms.

390
00:14:14,821 --> 00:14:17,357
Be true to myself?

391
00:14:17,357 --> 00:14:18,958
Allan, come back!

392
00:14:18,958 --> 00:14:20,393
What do you mean?

393
00:14:20,393 --> 00:14:23,162
Allan...be true?

394
00:14:23,162 --> 00:14:24,664
What?

395
00:14:24,664 --> 00:14:26,265
What does that mean?!

396
00:14:30,236 --> 00:14:42,415
♪

397
00:14:42,415 --> 00:14:45,151
Mocchi, you did
everything I told

398
00:14:45,151 --> 00:14:46,986
you to do in the match.

399
00:14:46,986 --> 00:14:52,825
♪

400
00:14:52,825 --> 00:14:56,963
You wore Small Worm right
down, then you attacked.

401
00:14:56,963 --> 00:14:58,464
Right, Chi.

402
00:14:58,464 --> 00:15:00,199
Double‐pounder!

403
00:15:00,199 --> 00:15:01,834
You should've won.

404
00:15:01,834 --> 00:15:03,970
So where did I go wrong?

405
00:15:03,970 --> 00:15:06,939
Weren't you strong enough
to defeat Small Worm?

406
00:15:06,939 --> 00:15:10,676
No, you were definitely
getting the better of him.

407
00:15:10,676 --> 00:15:12,445
(grunting)

408
00:15:12,445 --> 00:15:14,680
Cherry blossom blizzard!

409
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:17,617
♪

410
00:15:17,617 --> 00:15:18,851
Hang on.

411
00:15:18,851 --> 00:15:21,053
What did Allan do
during the match?

412
00:15:21,053 --> 00:15:23,356
♪

413
00:15:23,356 --> 00:15:25,024
Small Worm, don't give up!

414
00:15:26,626 --> 00:15:28,728
Move!

415
00:15:28,728 --> 00:15:29,929
Why?

416
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:33,299
Why did Small Worm
suddenly get so powerful?

417
00:15:33,299 --> 00:15:35,735
Summon courage, Chi.

418
00:15:35,735 --> 00:15:36,669
Chi!

419
00:15:36,669 --> 00:15:37,904
Chi.

420
00:15:37,904 --> 00:15:39,872
Be true to myself.

421
00:15:41,474 --> 00:15:42,775
I don't get it!

422
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:44,577
What's that mean?!

423
00:15:44,577 --> 00:15:46,212
Whoa!

424
00:15:46,212 --> 00:15:50,216
♪

425
00:15:50,216 --> 00:15:52,351
Summon courage?

426
00:15:52,351 --> 00:15:53,386
Courage?

427
00:15:54,754 --> 00:15:56,522
Huh?

428
00:15:56,522 --> 00:15:58,057
That's it.

429
00:15:58,057 --> 00:16:00,460
♪

430
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:02,895
Now I understand
what Allan meant.

431
00:16:02,895 --> 00:16:05,998
♪

432
00:16:05,998 --> 00:16:08,501
True to myself,
in other words...

433
00:16:08,501 --> 00:16:09,836
Chi?

434
00:16:09,836 --> 00:16:12,572
♪

435
00:16:12,572 --> 00:16:13,940
Genki!

436
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:15,775
Mocchi!

437
00:16:15,775 --> 00:16:19,479
Where are you?

438
00:16:19,479 --> 00:16:20,880
Anybody there?

439
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:24,250
Answer if you hear,
no, even if you can't.

440
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:26,319
♪

441
00:16:26,319 --> 00:16:28,588
I wonder if they're
both all right.

442
00:16:28,588 --> 00:16:30,890
No worry, Holly.

443
00:16:30,890 --> 00:16:32,291
You know them.

444
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:35,161
They'll show up sooner or later
acting like nothing's happened.

445
00:16:35,161 --> 00:16:37,763
(rumbling)

446
00:16:37,763 --> 00:16:39,866
What's going on?

447
00:16:39,866 --> 00:16:41,133
(Holly screams)

448
00:16:41,133 --> 00:16:43,669
Wood attack!

449
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:46,606
(gang shouts)

450
00:16:46,606 --> 00:16:49,842
Wood Golem,
I'll take you on.

451
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:52,812
It won't work, remember
what happened last time?

452
00:16:52,812 --> 00:16:55,281
(struggling)

453
00:16:55,281 --> 00:16:57,350
Wood attack!

454
00:16:57,350 --> 00:17:05,324
♪

455
00:17:05,324 --> 00:17:07,159
Oh, looks like a dead end.

456
00:17:08,961 --> 00:17:10,630
Anyone up for
a group prayer?

457
00:17:10,630 --> 00:17:13,165
♪

458
00:17:13,165 --> 00:17:16,269
(roars)

459
00:17:16,269 --> 00:17:17,570
Huh?

460
00:17:17,570 --> 00:17:30,249
♪

461
00:17:30,249 --> 00:17:32,752
(growling)

462
00:17:32,752 --> 00:17:35,087
Genki, Mocchi!

463
00:17:35,087 --> 00:17:37,523
Holly, sorry to keep you.

464
00:17:37,523 --> 00:17:39,258
Chi, Chi!

465
00:17:39,258 --> 00:17:40,993
Wood attack!

466
00:17:40,993 --> 00:17:42,395
Let's go, Mocchi.

467
00:17:42,395 --> 00:17:44,597
We'll show 'em what
courage is all about.

468
00:17:44,597 --> 00:17:45,598
Chi!

469
00:17:46,832 --> 00:17:49,168
(Genki shouts)

470
00:17:49,168 --> 00:17:56,208
♪

471
00:17:56,208 --> 00:17:58,277
Genki, Mocchi!

472
00:17:58,277 --> 00:18:01,247
Courage alone won't help
with this stick in the mud.

473
00:18:01,247 --> 00:18:04,450
You're right, he's much
stronger than any of us.

474
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:06,419
What are you guys talking about?

475
00:18:06,419 --> 00:18:08,054
If we don't protect
this mystery disk,

476
00:18:08,054 --> 00:18:09,655
then who will?

477
00:18:09,655 --> 00:18:11,123
Chi!

478
00:18:11,123 --> 00:18:12,792
(panting)

479
00:18:12,792 --> 00:18:20,399
♪

480
00:18:20,399 --> 00:18:22,768
We need to have more courage.

481
00:18:22,768 --> 00:18:26,005
♪

482
00:18:26,005 --> 00:18:28,107
‐Come on.
‐Chi!

483
00:18:28,107 --> 00:18:32,445
♪

484
00:18:32,445 --> 00:18:33,813
Genki!

485
00:18:33,813 --> 00:18:35,114
Mocchi!

486
00:18:35,114 --> 00:18:37,550
Go.

487
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:39,518
Summon your courage.

488
00:18:39,518 --> 00:18:40,987
Yeah!

489
00:18:42,655 --> 00:18:44,523
Wood attack!

490
00:18:44,523 --> 00:18:53,032
♪

491
00:18:53,032 --> 00:18:54,767
Now's a good time
for a group attack.

492
00:18:54,767 --> 00:18:57,970
Oh, yeah!

493
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:59,138
Dragon punch!

494
00:18:59,138 --> 00:19:01,173
Tongue slap!

495
00:19:01,173 --> 00:19:02,742
Lightning attack!

496
00:19:02,742 --> 00:19:06,412
♪

497
00:19:06,412 --> 00:19:08,714
Now is your chance.

498
00:19:08,714 --> 00:19:11,350
Mocchi, use your
Mocchi cannon.

499
00:19:11,350 --> 00:19:13,519
♪

500
00:19:13,519 --> 00:19:14,620
Ready?

501
00:19:14,620 --> 00:19:17,390
‐Yeah!
‐Yeah!

502
00:19:17,390 --> 00:19:20,259
Mocchi cannon!

503
00:19:20,259 --> 00:19:22,962
♪

504
00:19:22,962 --> 00:19:26,399
(rumbling, explosion)

505
00:19:26,399 --> 00:19:28,501
You're messing with
the wrong people,

506
00:19:28,501 --> 00:19:30,403
'cause we're invincible.

507
00:19:30,403 --> 00:19:31,937
So you can forget
about stealing

508
00:19:31,937 --> 00:19:33,839
the mystery disk from us.

509
00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:37,376
♪

510
00:19:37,376 --> 00:19:39,912
(Wood Golem cries)

511
00:19:39,912 --> 00:19:41,547
Oh, yeah!

512
00:19:41,547 --> 00:19:43,049
We won, we won!

513
00:19:43,049 --> 00:19:47,520
♪

514
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:50,122
I'm so glad you
two aren't hurt.

515
00:19:50,122 --> 00:19:53,059
Uh, I figured
something out.

516
00:19:53,059 --> 00:19:54,827
No sense having
all those plans

517
00:19:54,827 --> 00:19:56,729
if you don't
have any courage.

518
00:19:56,729 --> 00:19:59,298
I realized that my job
is to encourage everyone

519
00:19:59,298 --> 00:20:00,566
and give 'em hope.

520
00:20:00,566 --> 00:20:03,502
You're absolutely right.

521
00:20:03,502 --> 00:20:04,870
Hmm.

522
00:20:04,870 --> 00:20:07,573
I owe you one, Allan.

523
00:20:07,573 --> 00:20:08,841
Allan?

524
00:20:08,841 --> 00:20:10,843
He's the one who
gave me that advice.

525
00:20:10,843 --> 00:20:12,111
Right, Mocch?

526
00:20:12,111 --> 00:20:13,879
Mm‐hmm.

527
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:19,585
♪

528
00:20:19,585 --> 00:20:22,288
See ya again sometime, Genki.

529
00:20:22,288 --> 00:20:25,224
♪

530
00:20:25,224 --> 00:20:29,261
So, Allan's on a mission
to rescue mystery disks?

531
00:20:29,261 --> 00:20:31,864
I sure hope we can
meet up with him again.

532
00:20:31,864 --> 00:20:34,934
I'm sure we will,
sooner or later.

533
00:20:34,934 --> 00:20:36,202
Me too.

534
00:20:36,202 --> 00:20:38,037
Now, to Winner's Cup!

535
00:20:38,037 --> 00:20:40,306
Yeah, it's
practically in the bag.

536
00:20:40,306 --> 00:20:41,507
Let's do it!

537
00:20:41,507 --> 00:20:44,376
Come on, gang, we've got
a championship to win.

538
00:20:44,376 --> 00:20:46,912
(gang cheers)

539
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:49,281
♪ Monsters ♪

540
00:20:49,281 --> 00:20:50,850
♪ Monsters rule ♪

541
00:20:50,850 --> 00:21:15,574
♪

542
00:21:15,574 --> 00:21:17,109
♪ Monsters rule ♪

